Class DataSetGeneric<E extends Measurable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList<E>
          • DataSetGeneric<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - Type of elements to be held in this store
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>, java.util.RandomAccess
    public class DataSetGeneric<E extends Measurable>
extends java.util.ArrayList<E>

    A data store for elements of type E, which must implement the Measurable interface.

    Note that many methods, such as add, size, etc are provided by the ArrayList superclass. Their descriptions are omitted from this documentation.

    Author:
    parks

      • getList

        public java.util.List<E> getList()
        Accessor for the entire store.
        Returns:
        An ArrayList < E > of all elements in the data store. The ArrayList may be empty if the store has no elements, but should not be null.
